<div class="recipe">
<p>Everyone loves a good fudge. But who said fudge had to be hard to make? This recipe uses just 4 ingredients and takes less than 15 minutes. That's right, homemade fudge in just 15 minutes (plus time to let it set).</p>
<p>What makes a good fudge? For us, it has to have a deep and rich flavour, along with a silky smooth texture. Thankfully, peanut butter offers a lot of that on its own. All we need to do is firm it up.</p>
<p>You can take this recipe to the next level with some fairly easy additions, as well. Adding some chopped and toasted peanuts will give you a little more texture. Adding a chcolate ganache will give you that chocolate fix. Adding chrushed mini pretzels on top will add some more salty goodness. Really, you can't go wrong with anything you add - have fun with it!</p>   
