<div class="ingredients">
    <h3><strong>Ingredients</strong></h3>
    <ul>
       <li>1 cup unsalted butter (225g), plus more for greasing the pan</li>
       <li>1 cup smooth peanut butter (260g)</li>
       <li>1 teaspoon vanilla extract</li>
       <li>3 3/4 cups powdered sugar (455g)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3><strong>Directions</strong></h3>
    <ol>
        <li>Grease an 8" pan with butter. Trim a piece of parchment or wax paper to line the pan, try to leave some that goes up the sides to make it easier to grab and pull later.</li>
        <li>Combine the butter and peanut butter in a sizable microwave-safe bowl. Cover with plastic wrap and poke some vent holes in it for the steam to escape.</li>
        <li>Microwave for 2 minutes on high. Stir it well, then microwave for 2 minutes again - it will be hot, so be very careful.</li>
        <li>Add the powdered sugar and vanilla to the peanut butter mixture. It will be hard to stir and will firm up now.</li>
        <li>Spread the mixture into the prepared pan and cover with a layer of parchment or wax paper. Let cool in the fridge for 2 hours. Cut and store in an air tight container at room temperature for up to a week.</li>    
    </ol>
</div>
